íŸ@88bb7e65acf654169209cd91c43d7b06cabf3a94f489a07d064efd31d17f82c7⁄}Title: title: rm
Path: Examples
Content:
Delete, or move a file to the trash (based on the 'always_trash' config option).
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> rm file.txt


```
Move a file to the trash.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> rm --trash file.txt


```
Delete a file permanently, even if the 'always_trash' config option is true.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> rm --permanent file.txt


```
Delete a file, ignoring 'file not found' errors.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> rm --force file.txt


```
Delete all 0KB files in the current directory.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> ls | where size == 0KB and type == file | each { rm $in.name } | null


```
